nwhrDeviceTable.name: nwhrDeviceTable
nwhrDeviceTable.description: Extensions to the (conceptual) table of devices contained by the host

nwhrDeviceEntry.name: nwhrDeviceEntry
nwhrDeviceEntry.description: Extensions to a (conceptual) entry for one device contained by the host

nwhrDeviceAdapterIndex.name: nwhrDeviceAdapterIndex
nwhrDeviceAdapterIndex.description: The index into the nwhrAdapterTable of the adapter/controller to which this device is attached (or physically manifested by, for logical device). Zero if not applicable.

nwhrDeviceControllerNumber.name: nwhrDeviceControllerNumber
nwhrDeviceControllerNumber.description: The controller number (relative to its adapter), or the SCSI target ID, or zero if not applicable. Note that zero is a valid value for both controller number and SCSI Target ID.

nwhrDeviceNumber.name: nwhrDeviceNumber
nwhrDeviceNumber.description: The device number (relative to its controller), or the SCSI LUN (Logical Unit Number), or zero if not applicable. Note that zero is a valid value for both device number and SCSI LUN.

nwhrProcessorCount.name: nwhrProcessorCount
nwhrProcessorCount.description: The number of processor devices contained in this host

nwhrPrinterCount.name: nwhrPrinterCount
nwhrPrinterCount.description: The number of printer devices contained in this host

nwhrDiskStorageCount.name: nwhrDiskStorageCount
nwhrDiskStorageCount.description: The number of Disk Storage devices contained in this host.

nwhrDiskStorageHeads.name: nwhrDiskStorageHeads
nwhrDiskStorageHeads.description: The number of read/write heads on the drive

nwhrDiskStorageCylinders.name: nwhrDiskStorageCylinders
nwhrDiskStorageCylinders.description: The number of cylinders on the drive.

nwhrDiskStorageSectorsPerTrack.name: nwhrDiskStorageSectorsPerTrack
nwhrDiskStorageSectorsPerTrack.description: The number of sectors per track on the drive.

nwhrDiskStorageSectorSize.name: nwhrDiskStorageSectorSize
nwhrDiskStorageSectorSize.description: The size of a sector in bytes.

nwhrDiskStorageBlockSize.name: nwhrDiskStorageBlockSize
nwhrDiskStorageBlockSize.description: The driver maximum I/O request size in bytes.

nwhrPhysicalPartitionTable.name: nwhrPhysicalPartitionTable
nwhrPhysicalPartitionTable.description: A table of physical partitions for long-term storage devices contained by the host.

nwhrPhysicalPartitionEntry.name: nwhrPhysicalPartitionEntry
nwhrPhysicalPartitionEntry.description: An entry for one partition. The hrDeviceIndex in the index represents the entry in the hrDeviceTable that corresponds to the nwhrPhysicalPartitionEntry.

nwhrPhysicalPartitionIndex.name: nwhrPhysicalPartitionIndex
nwhrPhysicalPartitionIndex.description: A unique value for each physical partition on this long-term storage device. The value for each long-term storage device must remain constant from one re- initialization of the agent to the next re- initialization.

nwhrPhysicalPartitionType.name: nwhrPhysicalPartitionType
nwhrPhysicalPartitionType.description: The type of this physical partition.

nwhrPhysicalPartitionDescr.name: nwhrPhysicalPartitionDescr
nwhrPhysicalPartitionDescr.description: A textual description of this partition.

nwhrPhysicalPartitionSize.name: nwhrPhysicalPartitionSize
nwhrPhysicalPartitionSize.description: The size (in Kilobytes) of this physical partition.

nwhrHotfixTable.name: nwhrHotfixTable
nwhrHotfixTable.description: The table of hotfix areas of diskStorage devices contained by the host. Note that this table is potentially sparse: an entry exists if the corresponding value of the hrDeviceType object is `hrDeviceDiskStorage' and a NetWare partition exists on the device.

nwhrHotfixEntry.name: nwhrHotfixEntry
nwhrHotfixEntry.description: An entry for one hotfix redirection area contained by the host.

nwhrHotfixUnits.name: nwhrHotfixUnits
nwhrHotfixUnits.description: The size, in bytes, of the hotfix blocks.

nwhrHotfixTotal.name: nwhrHotfixTotal
nwhrHotfixTotal.description: The size of the total hotfix redirection area represented by this entry, in units of nwhrHotfixUnits.

nwhrHotfixUsed.name: nwhrHotfixUsed
nwhrHotfixUsed.description: The number of hotfix redirected blocks, i.e. the number of bad blocks that hotfix has found.

nwhrHotfixReserved.name: nwhrHotfixReserved
nwhrHotfixReserved.description: The number of hotfix redirection blocks reserved for system use.

nwhrAdapterCount.name: nwhrAdapterCount
nwhrAdapterCount.description: The number of adapters contained in this host.

nwhrAdapterTable.name: nwhrAdapterTable
nwhrAdapterTable.description: General information for each adapter board in the host: driver name and version, Interrupt, DMA, I/O address, and number of attached devices.

nwhrAdapterEntry.name: nwhrAdapterEntry
nwhrAdapterEntry.description: General information for a particular adapter board in the host: driver name and version, Interrupt, DMA, I/O address, and number of attached devices.

nwhrAdapterIndex.name: nwhrAdapterIndex
nwhrAdapterIndex.description: A unique value for each adapter contained in the host. The value for each adapter must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the agent to the next re-initialization.

nwhrAdapterType.name: nwhrAdapterType
nwhrAdapterType.description: An indication of the type of adapter. This will typically be one of the possible values of hrDeviceType.

nwhrAdapterDescr.name: nwhrAdapterDescr
nwhrAdapterDescr.description: A description the hardware for this adapter. This will usually include manufacturer, model, and version information. For LAN adapters, this could include the short board name and the boards burnt-in MAC address.

nwhrAdapterDriverDescr.name: nwhrAdapterDriverDescr
nwhrAdapterDriverDescr.description: A textual description of the driver for this adapter

nwhrAdapterDriverMajorVer.name: nwhrAdapterDriverMajorVer
nwhrAdapterDriverMajorVer.description: The major version number of the adapter driver.

nwhrAdapterDriverMinorVer.name: nwhrAdapterDriverMinorVer
nwhrAdapterDriverMinorVer.description: The minor version number of the adapter driver.

nwhrAdapterPort1.name: nwhrAdapterPort1
nwhrAdapterPort1.description: The primary I/O port block. This is the base address of a block of I/O addresses decoded by the adapter. The value will be zero if there is no I/O address associated with this adapter.

nwhrAdapterPort1Len.name: nwhrAdapterPort1Len
nwhrAdapterPort1Len.description: The number of I/O ports in the block starting at nwhrAdapterPort1. This value is used in conjunction with nwhrAdapterPort1 to determine the I/O block used by the adapter. The value will be zero if there is no I/O address associated with this adapter.

nwhrAdapterPort2.name: nwhrAdapterPort2
nwhrAdapterPort2.description: The secondary I/O port block. This is the base address of a block of I/O addresses decoded by the adapter. The value will be zero if there is no secondary I/O address associated with this adapter.

nwhrAdapterPort2Len.name: nwhrAdapterPort2Len
nwhrAdapterPort2Len.description: The number of I/O ports in the block starting at nwhrAdapterPort2. This value is used in conjunction with nwhrAdapterPort2 to determine the secondary I/O block used by the adapter. The value will be zero if there is no I/O address associated with this adapter.

nwhrAdapterMem1.name: nwhrAdapterMem1
nwhrAdapterMem1.description: The primary Memory Address. This is the base address of the primary block of memory space decoded by the adapter. The value will be zero if there is no memory address associated with this adapter.

nwhrAdapterMem1Len.name: nwhrAdapterMem1Len
nwhrAdapterMem1Len.description: The length, in bytes, of the primary memory address block. From this value and nwhrAdapterMem1, a determination can be made as to which memory address ranges are in use by the adapter.

nwhrAdapterMem2.name: nwhrAdapterMem2
nwhrAdapterMem2.description: The secondary Memory Address. This is the address of the secondary block of memory space decoded by the adapter. The value will be zero if there is no secondary memory address associated with this adapter.

nwhrAdapterMem2Len.name: nwhrAdapterMem2Len
nwhrAdapterMem2Len.description: The length, in bytes, of the secondary memory address block. From this value and nwhrAdapterMem2, a determination can be made as to which memory address ranges are in use by the adapter.

nwhrAdapterDMA1.name: nwhrAdapterDMA1
nwhrAdapterDMA1.description: The primary DMA channel used by the adapter. The value will be 255 if this adapter does not use any DMA channel.

nwhrAdapterDMA2.name: nwhrAdapterDMA2
nwhrAdapterDMA2.description: The secondary DMA channel used by the adapter. The value will be 255 if this adapter does not use a secondary DMA channel.

nwhrAdapterInterrupt1.name: nwhrAdapterInterrupt1
nwhrAdapterInterrupt1.description: The primary interrupt vector used by the adapter. The value will be 255 if this adapter does not use any Interrupt.

nwhrAdapterInterrupt2.name: nwhrAdapterInterrupt2
nwhrAdapterInterrupt2.description: The secondary interrupt vector used by the adapter. The value will be 255 if this adapter does not use a secondary Interrupt.

nwhrAdapterSlot.name: nwhrAdapterSlot
nwhrAdapterSlot.description: The slot in which the adapter resides. The value will be zero if the slot information is not available on the platform, such as an ISA based PC, otherwise the value will be the slot number the adapter resides. The slot number starts from 1.

nwhrAdapterDevices.name: nwhrAdapterDevices
nwhrAdapterDevices.description: The number of devices associated with this adapter. For instance, the number of drives attached to a disk controller.

nwhrMslCount.name: nwhrMslCount
nwhrMslCount.description: The number of Mirrored Server Link (MSL) devices contained in this host.

nwhrMslTable.name: nwhrMslTable
nwhrMslTable.description: The (conceptual) table of Mirrored Server Link (MSL) devices contained by the host. Note that this table is potentially sparse: a (conceptual) entry exists only if the corresponding value of the hrDeviceType object is nwhrDeviceMirroredServerLink

nwhrMslEntry.name: nwhrMslEntry
nwhrMslEntry.description: A (conceptual) entry for one Mirrored Server Link (MSL) device contained by the host. The hrDeviceIndex in the index represents the entry in the hrDeviceTable that corresponds to the nwhrMslEntry.

nwhrMslState.name: nwhrMslState
nwhrMslState.description: The current state of this MSL device.

nwhrMslSpeed.name: nwhrMslSpeed
nwhrMslSpeed.description: The nominal bandwidth of the MSL link in bits per second.

nwhrMslSends.name: nwhrMslSends
nwhrMslSends.description: The number of sends from this MSL device.

nwhrMslReceives.name: nwhrMslReceives
nwhrMslReceives.description: The number of receives by this MSL device.

nwhrMslInErrors.name: nwhrMslInErrors
nwhrMslInErrors.description: The number of errors in receives by this MSL device.

nwhrMslOutErrors.name: nwhrMslOutErrors
nwhrMslOutErrors.description: The number of errors on sends by this MSL device.

nwhrPrinterTable.name: nwhrPrinterTable
nwhrPrinterTable.description: A set of data for each accessible printer, whether local or remote.

nwhrPrinterEntry.name: nwhrPrinterEntry
nwhrPrinterEntry.description: A set of data for a particular printer.

nwhrPrinterID.name: nwhrPrinterID
nwhrPrinterID.description: A unique value for each accessible printer. This value will be constant for the lifetime of the mapping.

nwhrPrinterLocalName.name: nwhrPrinterLocalName
nwhrPrinterLocalName.description: The local name for the printer.

nwhrPrinterQueueName.name: nwhrPrinterQueueName
nwhrPrinterQueueName.description: The name of the print queue associated with this printer. Zero length string if printer is local.

nwhrPrinterServerName.name: nwhrPrinterServerName
nwhrPrinterServerName.description: The name of the server containing the print queue. Zero length string if printer is local.

nwhrPrinterTransportDomain.name: nwhrPrinterTransportDomain
nwhrPrinterTransportDomain.description: The transport domain associated with the printer (print queue).

nwhrPrinterTransportAddress.name: nwhrPrinterTransportAddress
nwhrPrinterTransportAddress.description: The transport address associated with this printer (print queue). Zero length string if printer is local.

nwhrPrinterDeviceIndex.name: nwhrPrinterDeviceIndex
nwhrPrinterDeviceIndex.description: The value of hrDeviceIndex for this printer. Zero if non-local.

nwhrLslOutPkts.name: nwhrLslOutPkts
nwhrLslOutPkts.description: The total number of of SendPacket requests made to the LSL.

nwhrLslInPkts.name: nwhrLslInPkts
nwhrLslInPkts.description: The total number of GetStackECB requests made by MLIDs to the LSL.

nwhrLslUnclaimedPkts.name: nwhrLslUnclaimedPkts
nwhrLslUnclaimedPkts.description: The total number of times a packet was received and not consumed by a protocol stack.

nwhrProtocolTable.name: nwhrProtocolTable
nwhrProtocolTable.description: The Protocol Table provides basic information about protocols running in the host, management stations should refer to the appropriate protocol MIBs for the details about each protocol.

nwhrProtocolName.name: nwhrProtocolName
nwhrProtocolName.description: The protocol name, for example, IPX, IP, ARP.

nwhrProtocolID.name: nwhrProtocolID
nwhrProtocolID.description: The protocol identifier For example: 000000000800 - IP for Ethernet II 00080007809B - AppleTalk for Ethernet SNAP

nwhrProtocolAddress.name: nwhrProtocolAddress
nwhrProtocolAddress.description: This object provides protocol address information, for example, the Network Address on IPX network, the IP address on IP network. Note there is no format in the InternationalDisplayString and the information is not guaranteed available.

nwhrProtocolOutPkts.name: nwhrProtocolOutPkts
nwhrProtocolOutPkts.description: The total number of send packet requests made to the LSL.

nwhrProtocolInPkts.name: nwhrProtocolInPkts
nwhrProtocolInPkts.description: The total number of incoming packets that were consumed by the protocol.

nwhrProtocolIgnoredPkts.name: nwhrProtocolIgnoredPkts
nwhrProtocolIgnoredPkts.description: The total number of times the protocol receive handler was called with look ahead and the protocol did not return a receive ECB to the MLID to receive the packet

nwhrProtocolFullName.name: nwhrProtocolFullName
nwhrProtocolFullName.description: The full name of the protocol name, for example, 'DOD Internet Protocol'.

nwhrIfTable.name: nwhrIfTable
nwhrIfTable.description: Extensions to MIB-II's Interfaces table to add some NetWare specific info.

nwhrIfEntry.name: nwhrIfEntry
nwhrIfEntry.description: NetWare specific info for a particular interface.

nwhrIfFrameType.name: nwhrIfFrameType
nwhrIfFrameType.description: The frame type for this logical board.

nwhrIfLogicalBoardName.name: nwhrIfLogicalBoardName
nwhrIfLogicalBoardName.description: The name assigned to this logical board.
